Classic text fixtures -- sources and licenses
=============================================

All classic fixtures contain ~100-200 lines of public-domain source text.

classic_arabic.txt
  Quran (Uthmani script, full tashkeel)
  amrayn/quran-text on GitHub
  https://github.com/amrayn/quran-text
  License: Public domain (religious text)

classic_chinese.txt
  Laozi, Dao De Jing (道德經), Wang Bi edition (~300 CE, text ~500 BCE)
  Chinese Wikisource (text itself public domain by age)
  https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/道德經_(王弼本)
  License: Public domain (author d. ~500 BCE)

classic_cyrillic.txt
  Alexander Pushkin, selected lyric poems (1820s-1830s)
  F0rgenet/rufish corpus on GitHub (text sourced from Pushkin's works)
  https://github.com/F0rgenet/rufish
  License: Public domain (author d. 1837)

classic_devanagari.txt
  Bhagavad Gita (श्रीमद्भगवद्गीता)
  sanskritdocuments.org
  https://sanskritdocuments.org/sanskrit/bhagavadgita/
  License: Public domain (see sanskritdocuments.org/license)

classic_greek.txt
  Homer, Iliad (ancient Greek text)
  Perseus Digital Library, Tufts University
  https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.01.0133
  License: Public domain (author ~8th century BCE)

classic_hebrew.txt
  Genesis (בראשית), Westminster Leningrad Codex
  openscriptures/morphhb on GitHub
  https://github.com/openscriptures/morphhb
  License: CC BY 4.0 (markup); text itself public domain (ancient religious text)

classic_japanese.txt
  Natsume Soseki, Botchan (坊っちゃん), 1906
  Aozora Bunko (青空文庫)
  https://www.aozora.gr.jp/cards/000148/card752.html
  License: Public domain (author d. 1916; PD in Japan)

classic_korean.txt
  Hunminjeongeum (훈민정음), 1446
  Korean Wikisource (text itself public domain by age, 1446)
  https://ko.wikisource.org/wiki/훈민정음
  License: Public domain (author King Sejong, d. 1450)
